<paragraph id="3FBD29ED688212DFD7A5C0E5A5DC5BB8" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">China (Yunnan).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8DB61AF8DFD7A20C008CB7041D8D3C37" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B3521EFA1E5FB6F5CB2A9D920443A6F5" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CD3F2E41467A63432DE7F3AD7D0845C9" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">The specific name, derived from Latin word meaning the broadest, refers to the forewing with an extremely broad band at apex.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="743131BC43298F63EFF31F3033C65AC4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="BB5B53B071ABE9F877D988B3BBC3E6FD" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA0371D8564315EC0C3BAA5D12B237B5" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4F8FC2AA8E3FE8E6EE8F5D77BD457FC1" genus="B." lsidName="B. latissimus" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species" species="latissimus">
<emphasis id="2D4FDDAD1C960CDF42E21EEE6CE2312D" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">B. latissimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="1A5A9743EDCD8EF3BEF348BE2958750A" genus="B." lsidName="B. herbaceus" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species" species="herbaceus">
<emphasis id="23B7DDCB13D6E8ABB5500809EE606CB2" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">B. herbaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Tsaur &amp; Hsu, 1991, but differs in: (1) left side of periandrium with two spinose processes (in 
<taxonomicName id="17700537BE246828339A9C9D9126ED29" genus="B." lsidName="B. herbaceus" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species" species="herbaceus">
<emphasis id="0183ECF7C21EB38E50A545B89941071D" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">B. herbaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, left side of periandrium with one spinose process); (2) spinose process on right of periandrium curved downwards (in 
<taxonomicName id="F7995E802EC2506BE0B00D05E6FD8AB5" genus="B." lsidName="B. herbaceus" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="species" species="herbaceus">
<emphasis id="312CF1D70C6B11AED2426566F9D4A74D" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">B. herbaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, spinose process in the same position curved upwards); (3) anal segment asymmetrical (the latter symmetrical); (4) forewing with one blackish brown spot and two bands (the latter without any marking).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
